Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.76,0:00:12.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.59,0:00:13.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} has...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.47,0:00:15.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come back to life!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.34,0:00:18.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.69,0:00:25.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Causing your eyelids to swell and permeating your heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.88,0:00:27.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tear drops serve as a prelude to a wealth of drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.30,0:00:31.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An unforeseen development, a deepening\Nmystery, and a second locked room!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.94,0:00:33.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.61,0:00:35.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.49,0:00:37.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.72,0:02:24.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After losing our way, we happened across a bizarre mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.81,0:02:32.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A séance for summoning the spirit of Miyahara Kira san, an idol\Nwho died in an accident a year earlier, was being held there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.40,0:02:38.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason was that rumors concerning Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Ncurse were spreading among the fan club members...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.90,0:02:43.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And with the addition of a murder, it prompted\Nthem to ascertain the cause of the events.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.62,0:02:47.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although the phenomenon that occurred\Nduring the séance were just tricks...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.29,0:02:51.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There seems to be a reason hidden behind Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s death.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.25,0:02:55.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And late at night, in the meditation\Nroom where the séance had been held...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.38,0:03:00.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of the participants, Utakura\NShouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was found murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.60,0:03:10.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,THE SÊANCE'S DOUBLE LOCKED ROOM MYSTERY CASE
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.60,0:03:10.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,(SECOND LOCKED ROOM)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.52,0:03:17.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hoonogi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.57,0:03:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.90,0:03:20.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.86,0:03:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.37,0:03:26.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} is dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.04,0:03:29.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like he's dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.83,0:03:30.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.37,0:03:32.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.83,0:03:35.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.34,0:03:36.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.21,0:03:38.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Too"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.01,0:03:40.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.88,0:03:43.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.43,0:03:44.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inside this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.22,0:03:49.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.85,0:03:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.93,0:03:51.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Show me the place!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.52,0:03:56.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I received a strange email, I went\Nto visit Sensei's room to consult with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.81,0:04:00.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But his room was locked, and he didn't reply even when I knocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.53,0:04:05.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I was wondering what to do, I heard a\Ncell phone ringtone coming from the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.82,0:04:07.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A ringtone?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.20,0:04:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since that was from Shouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s cell\Nphone, I felt something was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.66,0:04:15.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I peeked into the room from the\Nwindow went above the door and...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.96,0:04:20.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You saw Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.17,0:04:21.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.30,0:04:29.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, it's not something a kid should see!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.19,0:04:37.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.32,0:04:40.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.61,0:04:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.99,0:04:45.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's the key?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.12,0:04:48.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only Sensei has it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.83,0:04:50.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.04,0:04:56.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have anything to pry open the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.58,0:04:59.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a toolbox in the utility closet at the end of the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.09,0:05:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.36,0:05:20.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.65,0:05:25.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.95,0:05:28.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are posters.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.66,0:05:31.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They look like the posters of Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nfrom inside the meditation room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.10,0:05:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of these?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.95,0:05:39.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone brought these posters from the meditation\Nroom, ripped them into pieces and scattered around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.96,0:05:42.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would they want to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.93,0:05:57.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How's Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.94,0:06:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.02,0:06:03.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.65,0:06:04.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.94,0:06:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.36,0:06:12.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this the rope used to murder Shouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.66,0:06:18.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim is Utakurâ Shouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.54,0:06:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was told she was an aspiring gravure idol.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.17,0:06:25.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Utakura Shouko?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.71,0:06:27.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The name sounds familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.92,0:06:33.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was the primary discoverer of the editor\Nmurder case t hat occurred half a month ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.68,0:06:37.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the case Shiratori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} handled.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.56,0:06:38.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.77,0:06:44.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems the victim left a bloody\Nmessage of "Kira" at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.86,0:06:48.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this is the message sent to everyone\Nprior to the discovery of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.70,0:06:51.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It says "Kira" too, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.49,0:06:55.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does this mean it's related to the case Shiratori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} took charge of?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.12,0:06:59.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've discovered strange gadgets all over the place in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.21,0:07:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those are the gimmicks used in the séance trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.38,0:07:05.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Séance?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.71,0:07:08.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean a ritual to summon a spirit of the dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.84,0:07:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.34,0:07:13.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Last night they conducted a séance right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.22,0:07:21.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The spirit they attempted to summon was that of an idol\Nactress that died in an accident last year: Miyahara Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.77,0:07:23.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miyahara Kira?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.40,0:07:26.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not familiar with her, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.82,0:07:30.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she's said to have been a charismatic figure that\Nenjoyed great popularity on numerous cosplay sites.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.32,0:07:35.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By cosplay, you mean people dressing\Nup as manga or anime characters?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.20,0:07:37.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.49,0:07:42.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, before her death, she was in\Nthe gravure and acting business...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.29,0:07:44.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which had her surrounded by a number of fanatic fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.38,0:07:46.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.42,0:07:48.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did they conduct a séance?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.55,0:07:53.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Recently, weird rumors began spreading\Namongst members of her fan club.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.09,0:07:55.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About a curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.22,0:07:57.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A curse?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.56,0:08:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even that editor's murder mentioned earlier has\N\Nsparked rumors that Kira's curse caused it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.81,0:08:08.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Prompting them to summon her spirit\Nin an attempt to flesh out the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.77,0:08:10.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.40,0:08:12.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did the spirit come out?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.07,0:08:14.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How on earth could it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.03,0:08:15.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was all a hoax.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.57,0:08:18.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ones who set the trick were Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Hoonogi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.91,0:08:23.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems their intention was to surprise everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.04,0:08:29.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But'they said that someone else swapped the\Ncontent of Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s recordings used in the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.84,0:08:36.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall rise from the dead tonight...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.36,0:08:41.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And with my hands, I shall wreak my vengeance!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.10,0:08:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was most likely the culprit's doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.27,0:08:54.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They pretended to be Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who died in\Nan accident, and went on a murder spree.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.07,0:08:59.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's one more thing that struck me as odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.87,0:09:02.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't detect any defensive wounds on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.62,0:09:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I found on the body's neck was a ligature\Nmark produced by the constriction of a thin rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.71,0:09:15.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps she was drugged to sleep and murdered by strangulation?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.14,0:09:22.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, this really is a strange room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.97,0:09:25.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This place is known as the meditation room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.39,0:09:29.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would shut himself in here when\Nhe needed to think of a plot for his manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.81,0:09:35.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it true that this room was completely\Nsealed at the time of the body's discovery?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.15,0:09:35.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.78,0:09:39.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only entrance to this room is through these doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.37,0:09:43.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a padlock on the inner side of the doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.20,0:09:48.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the only person who owned the\Nkey to the padlock was Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.42,0:09:53.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't locate any key from this room as of yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.05,0:09:55.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although there's a ventilation window above...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.80,0:09:58.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There isn't a foothold around in order to reach that high.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.05,0:10:02.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would it be possible if they used the easels and chairs in the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.14,0:10:07.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They wouldn't reach the window even if\Nthey climbed up the easel atop a chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.27,0:10:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if they somehow did, evidence of the\Nfoothold should still be under the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.06,0:10:13.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But apparently there aren't any.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.15,0:10:17.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, the window is powered by electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.15,0:10:20.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One would have to use the switch here to open and close it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.20,0:10:27.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if you let go of your finger from the switch...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.37,0:10:30.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.83,0:10:32.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same goes for closing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.88,0:10:37.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you don't hold the switch the entire time, you\Nwon't be able to completely shut the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.84,0:10:41.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So no one was able to escape from that window, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.59,0:10:43.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, how did the culprit do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.28,0:10:46.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying it was Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s spirit after all!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.43,0:10:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way that can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.73,0:10:53.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A perfectly locked room?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.91,0:11:02.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.32,0:11:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the meditation room last night, they had tens of\Nposters with Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} on them as decorative props.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.00,0:11:13.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently someone brought those in and scattered the pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.50,0:11:15.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would they want to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.30,0:11:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.96,0:11:18.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How is it, Chiba?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.59,0:11:22.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We suspect that he was poisoned by cyanide compounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.72,0:11:24.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Traces of those can be found in his wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.72,0:11:29.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure that this room was also locked without a doubt?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.02,0:11:30.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.10,0:11:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Again, none other than Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had the key to this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.94,0:11:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had no choice but to prop the door open.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.69,0:11:38.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you find the key?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.61,0:11:42.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't in the desk drawers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.03,0:11:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only place left to search is the drawer over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.66,0:11:47.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The drawer is locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.33,0:11:52.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've opened it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.88,0:11:57.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've found the keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.10,0:12:08.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like this is the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.10,0:12:11.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I can't turn the key since the cylinder was\Ndamaged when the door was forced open.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.56,0:12:16.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was informed that the key was made in\NGermany and cannot be easily duplicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.44,0:12:19.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like in order to lock this door...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.98,0:12:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You need the key to lock it both from\Nthe outside and from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.70,0:12:25.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, seems so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.53,0:12:28.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other, key is probably for that padlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.70,0:12:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go confirm it at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.20,0:12:32.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.75,0:12:35.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the rope on the floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.58,0:12:38.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They won't find out until they ruh\Na test and confirm a match, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.50,0:12:42.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They are confident it was the murder weapon\Nused to strangle Utakura Shouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.80,0:12:43.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the windows?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.30,0:12:46.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They are locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.76,0:12:51.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, since they are all iron-barred on the\Noutside, it's impossible to go through there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.22,0:12:53.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A locked room here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.19,0:12:55.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.35,0:13:01.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The window vent is only good for about ten\Ncentimeters, making this door the only entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.40,0:13:06.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since the key to the door was in the\Ndrawer in the room, which was also locked...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.57,0:13:09.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.41,0:13:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we look at it from a different angle, this\Nlocked room mystery is as good as solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.00,0:13:13.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.50,0:13:16.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.00,0:13:18.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.50,0:13:21.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit who killed Shouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was Hirasaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.80,0:13:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then returned to this room, locked\Nthe door, and drank the poisoned wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.26,0:13:28.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.68,0:13:33.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's highly probable that the one responsible for\Neditor Sawanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s murder was also Hirasaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.14,0:13:37.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he left a dying message of "Kira" at the scene, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.81,0:13:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was actually written by Hirasaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.40,0:13:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who sent emails from Shouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Ncell phone was Hirasaka as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.53,0:13:52.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy did it with the intention to make it appear that his manga\Nprotagonist came to life and repeatedly committed murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.08,0:13:56.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he wouldn't seal this room if that were true no?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.04,0:13:58.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we'd conclude that it was suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.50,0:14:02.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His manga series—was it the "Blackmagic Girl"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.04,0:14:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The protagonist, Kira, is a witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.84,0:14:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he wanted people to think it was an\Nimpossible crime committed with the help of magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.76,0:14:13.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That kind of makes sense, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.68,0:14:14.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.52,0:14:17.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you figure out the other locked room mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.69,0:14:20.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No no, that one's not solved yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.56,0:14:21.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.15,0:14:26.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the only person with a key to\Nthe meditation room was Hirasaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.57,0:14:30.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the séance, I saw him locking the\Ndoor from the outside with the padlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.53,0:14:34.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one other than Hirasaka could have entered that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.04,0:14:43.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if we assume it was suicide, would he really go as\Nfar as to put the key in the drawer and lock it as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.63,0:14:51.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And why did he have to tear apart and\Nscatter all the posters of Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.02,0:15:04.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.44,0:15:08.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I apologize for the inconvenience,\Nbut I have some questions for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.01,0:15:11.90,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mifune Ryuuichi (27)\NCameraman
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.01,0:15:11.90,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Yatsukawa Kouji (27)\NNichiuri TV Assistant Director
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.82,0:15:14.28,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Earlier in the day, Utakura Shouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nwas found murdered at 1:00 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.41,0:15:14.28,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hoonogi Kazuo (28)\NKira Fan / Doctor
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.74,0:15:17.33,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kani Yutaka (24)\NFan Club Chairman / Figurine Creator
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.99,0:15:18.29,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,After that, Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was also found dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.70,0:15:19.87,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Izumi Maho (22)\NKira Fan
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.95,0:15:24.08,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The estimated time of their deaths was approximately\Nbetween the hours of 11:00 PM and 1:00 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.08,0:15:28.50,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,As such, I'd like to hear about your actions\Nand whereabouts during that period of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.09,0:15:34.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the séance last night the atmosphere was kind of spoiled...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.64,0:15:37.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everybody went back to their rooms early.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.52,0:15:40.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was about 10:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.68,0:15:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was in my room waiting enthusiastically\Nfor Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} to come back to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.32,0:15:48.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't even fall asleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.07,0:15:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, Mifune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and I were chatting with\NMouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} for a while, and left at 11:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.70,0:16:00.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You called Shouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} back then, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.83,0:16:03.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you confirm the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.75,0:16:04.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.50,0:16:09.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was 10:40 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.38,0:16:11.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she had a headache during that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.55,0:16:15.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Maho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went to check on her later, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.80,0:16:17.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.93,0:16:23.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was worried, so I peeked into her\Nroom, but Shouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wasn't inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.10,0:16:31.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since my room was next to hers, I was waiting for her to\Nreturn all that time in order to give her some medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.90,0:16:36.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she didn't come back no matter how long waited,\Nso I got worried and approached Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.99,0:16:41.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did any of you see Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} after the séance?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.38,0:16:48.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.63,0:16:52.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before I returned to my room, I visited\NSensei's room to have a little chat with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.38,0:16:54.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What were you chatting about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.18,0:17:01.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About the recording of Kira we played at the\Nséance that was switched by someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.35,0:17:04.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I headed to my room about fifteen minutes later.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.06,0:17:09.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, what made you guys decide to do a séance?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.40,0:17:12.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What made us?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.15,0:17:17.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you, strange rumors regarding Kira's\Ncurse were circulating in the fan club.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.28,0:17:19.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even a murder occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.45,0:17:22.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you seriously believe there are ghosts and curses?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.00,0:17:23.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.25,0:17:28.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed, it doesn't sound like something a normal adult would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.46,0:17:31.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you have some other purposes you're not telling me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.84,0:17:33.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.47,0:17:36.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, Hoonogi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.26,0:17:39.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you mention you received some strange phone calls before?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.55,0:17:40.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.26,0:17:43.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that, Yatsukawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.56,0:17:45.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.27,0:17:47.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was about a month ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.69,0:17:50.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We happened to bump into each other and drank at a snack bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.98,0:17:53.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.91,0:17:58.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.49,0:18:02.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Recently, I've been getting annoying phone calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.70,0:18:04.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder who did this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.95,0:18:07.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.83,0:18:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were being threatened by someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.75,0:18:12.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.55,0:18:18.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it Sawanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nalso received some strange letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.47,0:18:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.93,0:18:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About a month ago, I visited his publishing\Ncompany for a magazine discussion meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.02,0:18:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sawanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.44,0:18:30.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you heard about the rumors?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.52,0:18:31.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rumors?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.98,0:18:39.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been said members of my fan club that moved on to\Nother idols would begin to suffer from injuries and illnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.66,0:18:45.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Among those who were injured, some\Nwere saying they saw Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.54,0:18:48.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Such nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.33,0:18:52.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} turned into a vile ghost and\Njinxed the fans who ditched her for another idol?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.30,0:18:56.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not again...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.71,0:18:59.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.34,0:19:02.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.97,0:19:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just some tasteless prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.31,0:19:08.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did he really say, "Not again"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.31,0:19:13.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sawanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was threatened by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.11,0:19:14.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he was later murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.77,0:19:18.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hoonogi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.40,0:19:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.99,0:19:22.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please tell us the truth now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.03,0:19:28.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that I was being threatened.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.20,0:19:30.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of threat?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.33,0:19:37.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kira didn't die from a car acccident, but\Nrather in the party you had here..."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.13,0:19:42.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"And the one who hid Kira's body was Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}," they said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.64,0:19:45.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall, similar rumors were on the internet too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.76,0:19:50.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think that's the work of someone who mistook them as the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.77,0:19:54.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sawanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} were both being threatened.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.56,0:19:58.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But those were just ridiculous, baseless rumors!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.19,0:20:01.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite that, Sawanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} ended up dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.28,0:20:04.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the intimidator is our culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.16,0:20:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that you gathered everyone\Nhere in order to find your intimidator?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.33,0:20:12.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the excuse of conducting a séance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.17,0:20:15.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that really true?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.92,0:20:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.88,0:20:21.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After talking to Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}, we determined:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.67,0:20:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fanatic Kira fan—Kani{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.64,0:20:30.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The two girls who venerate Kira's\Ncharm—Shouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Maho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.73,0:20:36.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Along with the TV station assistant an director,\NYatsukawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}—they were all suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.31,0:20:37.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mifune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.69,0:20:39.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that the reason you gathered us all here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.98,0:20:41.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.58,0:20:52.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Let's scare them with the séance and watch their reactions."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.45,0:20:53.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.00,0:20:58.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fact that the voice of Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} you\Nset up was swapped by someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.34,0:21:01.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Means that your intimidator really\Nwas among the participants, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.84,0:21:05.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's very likely the culprit in Sawanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Ncase is also responsible for these crimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.47,0:21:10.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s family or intimate\Nfriends believed in the internet rumors and...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.52,0:21:13.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kira didn't have a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.48,0:21:15.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They died in a car accident when she was young.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.90,0:21:20.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why Kira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} was more\Ninto safe driving than anyone else!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.57,0:21:21.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems so.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.19,0:21:28.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle, why don't you ask them to show us\NSawanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s dying message of "Kira"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.20,0:21:29.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps we can learn something from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.12,0:21:34.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.16,0:21:35.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.54,0:21:37.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.79,0:21:38.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.50,0:21:39.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.13,0:21:44.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.92,0:21:48.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This key is for that padlock just like we suspected.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.97,0:21:49.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.93,0:21:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And as for this rope found in Hirasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.06,0:21:57.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They confirmed it was used to kill Utakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.23,0:21:58.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.85,0:22:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, Hirasaka was our guy just as I deduced.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.02,0:22:06.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, as long as we don't solve the\Nmystery of the other locked room...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.86,0:22:10.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't there a secret passage or something\Nalong those lines in the meditation room?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.45,0:22:12.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How is something like that possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.04,0:22:16.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I had them send the dying message via photo mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.38,0:22:25.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.59,0:22:29.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me, that person is the culprit?
